tweets.text: Elite league is not eating the prize pool share. French Devs are not biased toward Whales. It is just business. If you play @fantasy_top_, you know we are having hyperinflation in Cards. The total supply used to be 180k last year, now we are at 280k. We have burn and upgrade mechanics to balance the supply flow, but it is not enough. Reverse league is fun, but it incentivizes players to NOT burn useless cards, and creates an overhang supply on the marketplace. Elite, on the other hand, is harder and harder to compete. You are required to upgrade constantly, in order to maintain your portfolio strength. The final target is Legendary cards, which equals 125 common cards. For a deck with 5 Legendary cards, 625 commons were burned. Think about it, you are running a business. One customer group buys and re-buys your product constantly, another buys, gets the promotion, and is more likely to re-sell on eBay. Which one should you reward more? It is just business.
tweets.raw_text:
Elite league is not eating the  prize pool share.

French Devs are not biased toward Whales. 

It is just business.

If you play @fantasy_top_, you know we are having hyperinflation in Cards. The total supply used to be 180k last year, now we are at 280k.

We have burn and upgrade mechanics to balance the supply flow, but it is not enough.

Reverse league is fun, but it incentivizes players to NOT burn useless cards, and creates an overhang supply on the marketplace.

Elite, on the other hand, is harder and harder to compete. You are required to upgrade constantly, in order to maintain your portfolio strength.

The final target is Legendary cards, which equals 125 common cards. For a deck with 5 Legendary cards, 625 commons were burned.

Think about it, you are running a business. One customer group buys and re-buys your product constantly, another buys, gets the promotion, and is more likely to re-sell on eBay.

Which one should you reward more? 

It is just business.

tweets.text: üß† A few thoughts on the recent points update from @virtuals_io core dev. I completely agree with the first 2 points: ‚úÖ USD-based point system = real economic skin in the game ‚úÖ Relative Ranking Leaderboard = a BIG win for transparency A live, on-chain leaderboard helps kill FUD, favoritism, and drama. But 2 key areas still lack clarity. Right now, it‚Äôs still full of ambiguity üëá üëá üîπ (A) ‚ÄúAgents with good Product and fundamentals get more points‚Äù Sounds great. But‚Ä¶ what does ‚Äúgood‚Äù actually mean? ‚Ä¢ What are the KPIs? ‚Ä¢ Is there a public scoring or ranking system? ‚Ä¢ Who decides what‚Äôs good ‚Äî and based on what? If it‚Äôs done behind closed doors, that‚Äôs not merit-based. That‚Äôs bias. üì¢ Publish the criteria. Publish the project rankings/score/points. Let data decide. üîπ (B) ‚ÄúDev wallets don‚Äôt get points‚Äù Love the intent. But it needs precision: ‚Ä¢ Is a ‚Äúdev‚Äù the wallet that launched the agent and received the dev allocation from it‚Äôs own project? ‚Ä¢ What if the dev bought tokens from the market with their own funds, using their personal wallet? ‚Ä¢ Are foundation/treasury wallets excluded too? Since it‚Äôs not personal dev wallet, but Company Holding? üì¢ Define ‚Äúdev wallet‚Äù publicly, add wallet tagging on it. We need a public definition. On-chain, verifiable. No double standards. No grey areas. No favoritism. Conclusion: Let the system be: ‚úÖ Fair ‚úÖ Transparent ‚úÖ Accountable No backroom decisions. No hidden hands.
tweets.raw_text:
üß† A few thoughts on the recent points update from @virtuals_io core dev.

I completely agree with the first 2 points:
‚úÖ USD-based point system = real economic skin in the game
‚úÖ Relative Ranking Leaderboard = a BIG win for transparency

A live, on-chain leaderboard helps kill FUD, favoritism, and drama.

But 2 key areas still lack clarity. Right now, it‚Äôs still full of ambiguity üëá
üëá

üîπ (A) ‚ÄúAgents with good Product and  fundamentals get more points‚Äù

Sounds great. But‚Ä¶ what does ‚Äúgood‚Äù actually mean?

‚Ä¢  What are the KPIs?
‚Ä¢  Is there a public scoring or ranking system?
‚Ä¢  Who decides what‚Äôs good ‚Äî and based on what?

If it‚Äôs done behind closed doors, that‚Äôs not merit-based. That‚Äôs bias.

üì¢ Publish the criteria. Publish the project rankings/score/points.  Let data decide.

üîπ (B) ‚ÄúDev wallets don‚Äôt get points‚Äù

Love the intent. But it needs precision:

‚Ä¢  Is a ‚Äúdev‚Äù the wallet that launched the agent and received the dev allocation from it‚Äôs own project? 
‚Ä¢  What if the dev bought tokens from the market with their own funds, using their personal wallet?
‚Ä¢  Are foundation/treasury wallets excluded too? Since it‚Äôs not personal dev wallet, but Company Holding?

üì¢ Define ‚Äúdev wallet‚Äù publicly, add wallet tagging on it. We need a public definition. On-chain, verifiable. 

No double standards. No grey areas. No favoritism.

Conclusion:

Let the system be:
‚úÖ Fair
‚úÖ Transparent
‚úÖ Accountable

No backroom decisions. No hidden hands.

Study $AAVE $SKY $MORPHO $AERO. The problem is the failure of degenerate gamblers on this app (I am one) to focus on what clearly works in crypto -- DeFi. Right now, most humans live under oppressive financial regimes who max extract for government leaders and prevent humans from building value. If this industry spent the next five years entirely focused on building DeFi, it would dramatically change the world. It would collapse oppressive regimes, give billions of people financial control versus their oppressive government regimes, and provide the capital tools to unlock the greatest entrepreneurial time and advancements in human history. We cannot fathom what happens when billions of humans have financial control of their lives. It will be remarkable. The infighting among a small subset of crypto degenerate gamblers currently on X (which I am one) will fade. We will become nearly irrelevant in the next decade, a niche within a niche, compared to the behemoth that is expanding global finance to encompass every person and company, onchain in DeFi. The things we talk about like memecoins, NFTs, AI ponzis, gaming, etc., have a future, but their most important role will be to battle test DeFi before it puts the entire world onchain. You see, there are no problems with crypto because we found already found the product to change the world. It's DeFi. Always has been.
